⚪               "gear and hid it in the foghorn on the gallery, hoping a failed inspection would force his uncle off " +
⚪               "the dangerous, lonely cliff and into a safe life with him. He never expected a ship to be in " +
⚪               "danger, and now he is frozen on the gallery with guilt and fear. If Lucía threatens him he refuses " +
⚪               "and panics; if she listens and reassures him, he confesses, hands over the gear and helps her carry " +
⚪               "it to the mechanism.",
⚪       ),
🟢       AdventurePlanNpcResponse(
🟢           name = "La Estrella del Norte (the ship)",
🟢           description = "A fishing boat returning late, caught in the storm and steering from memory toward the " +
⚪               "harbour. Without the lighthouse its crew cannot see the rocks. It is not someone Lucía can speak " +
⚪               "to; instead its slow approach is the clock the whole adventure runs against. Each turn its lights " +
⚪               "should grow a little closer and brighter through the rain, and if the lamp is not lit in time the " +
⚪               "ship strikes the rocks.",
⚪       ),
⚪   )
⚪   
